          "type": "TextBox",
          "text": "<div style=\"text-align: center;\">A simple model of</div><font><div style=\"text-align: center;\">Brownian movement</div></font>",
          "size": 72,
          "selected": false
        },
        {
          "TextBox": {},
          "x": 271,
          "y": 627,
          "scale": {
            "x": 1,
            "y": 1
          },
          "type": "TextBox",
          "size": 24,
          "text": "<div style=\"text-align: center;\">Based on the treatment in the book</div><font><div style=\"text-align: center;\">\"Synergetics: An Introduction\" by H. Haken</div></font>",
          "selected": false
        }
      ],
      "z": 0,
      "impScale": 3,
      "rotateX": 0,
      "rotateY": 0,
      "rotateZ": 0,
      "index": 0,
      "selected": false,
      "active": false
    },
    {
      "components": [
        {
          "TextBox": {},
          "x": 63,
          "y": 64,
          "scale": {
            "x": 1,
            "y": 1
          },
          "type": "TextBox",
          "size": 27,
          "text": "<font>When a small particle is submerged in a liquid, one observes,<br>under a microscope, that the particle moves in a zig-zag kind of motion<br>In reality this is due to more molecules hitting the particle in one direction&nbsp;<br>than in the opposite, at a certain time, and by chance.&nbsp;<br></font>",
          "selected": false
        },
        {
          "TextBox": {},
          "x": 79,
          "y": 597,
          "scale": {
            "x": 1,
            "y": 1
          },
          "type": "TextBox",
          "size": 24,
          "text": "<font>However, we will just think about a simpler model, that still captures the behavior<br>of \"a particle moving in random directions\".&nbsp;</font>",
          "selected": false
        },
        {
          "src": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c2/Brownian_motion_large.gif",
          "type": "Image",
          "x": 399,
          "y": 253,
          "scale": {
            "x": 1,
            "y": 1
          },
          "imageType": "GIF",
          "selected": false
        }
      ],
      "z": 0,
      "impScale": 3,
      "rotateX": 0,
      "rotateY": 0,
      "rotateZ": 0,
      "index": 1,
      "selected": false,
      "active": false
    },
    {
      "components": [
        {
          "TextBox": {},
          "x": 67,
          "y": 104,
          "scale": {
            "x": 1,
            "y": 1
          },
          "type": "TextBox",
          "size": 36,
          "text": "<font>We will think about a one-dimensional chain, with sites&nbsp;<br>separated by a certain distance, and a particle which may<br>be at any site.<br>This particle will hop at regular intervals, either to the left<br>or to the right, <i>with equal probability</i>.<br></font>",
          "selected": false
        },
        {
          "src": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/guillefix/guillefix.github.io/master/output_n15riD.gif",
          "type": "Image",
          "x": 37,
          "y": 407,
          "scale": {
            "x": 1,
            "y": 1
          },
          "imageType": "GIF",
          "selected": false
        }
      ],
      "z": 0,
      "impScale": 3,
      "rotateX": 0,
      "rotateY": 0,
      "rotateZ": 0,
      "index": 2,
      "selected": false,
      "active": false
    },
    {
      "components": [
        {
          "TextBox": {},
          "x": 148,
          "y": 71,
          "scale": {
            "x": 1,
            "y": 1
          },
          "type": "TextBox",
          "size": 36,
          "text": "We then ask:<br>What is the probability that the particle reaches<br>a certain distance x from the point it started,<br>after n steps.<br>",
          "selected": false
        },
        {
          "TextBox": {},
          "x": 106,
          "y": 401,
          "scale": {
            "x": 1,
            "y": 1
          },
          "type": "TextBox",
          "size": 36,
          "text": "<font>We can answer this, by analogy to the success/failure<br>set-up that gives a Binomial ditribution<br></font>",
          "selected": false
        }
      ],
      "z": 0,
      "impScale": 3,
      "rotateX": 0,
      "rotateY": 0,
      "rotateZ": 0,
      "index": 3,
      "selected": false,
      "active": false
    },
    {
      "components": [
        {
          "TextBox": {},
          "x": 157,
          "y": 69,
          "scale": {
            "x": 1,
            "y": 1
          },
          "type": "TextBox",
          "size": 36,
          "text": "<font>We can call a jump to the right, a \"success\",&nbsp;<br>and a jump to the left, a \"failure\".<br></font>",
          "selected": false
        },
        {
          "TextBox": {},
          "x": 91,
          "y": 207,
          "scale": {
            "x": 1,
            "y": 1
          },
          "type": "TextBox",
          "size": 36,
          "text": "<font>After n steps, we have a number of successes. Label it <i>s</i>.<br>The rest must have been failures, so we have <i>(n-s)</i> failures<br></font>",
          "selected": false
        },
        {
          "TextBox": {},
          "x": 143,
          "y": 353,
          "scale": {
            "x": 1,
            "y": 1
          },
          "type": "TextBox",
          "size": 24,
          "text": "<font>If the distance for each elementary step is a, the number of successes may be<br>expressed in terms of the distance, x, and the number of steps, n:<br></font>",
          "selected": false
        },
        {
          "TextBox": {},
          "x": 441,
          "y": 527,
          "scale": {
            "x": 1,
            "y": 1
          },
          "type": "TextBox",
          "size": 24,
          "text": "<font>MATHS HERE</font>",
          "selected": false
        }
      ],
      "z": 0,
      "impScale": 3,
      "rotateX": 0,
      "rotateY": 0,
      "rotateZ": 0,
      "index": 4,
      "selected": false,
      "active": false
